<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-59-1075 </DOCNO><TEXT>This book is a reference on the engineering and economic aspects of gas-firedcogeneration systems. In its 44 chapters it covers equipment considerationsand applications for gas engines, gas turbines, steam engines, electricalswitchgear, and packaged systems. The text is illustrated with case studiesfor both commercial and industrial applications of all sizes, as wellas for packaged systems for restaurants and hospitals. A special chapteris included which illustrates market opportunities and keys to successfuldevelopment.</TEXT></DOC>